Admin Prompt:
AI Agent Prompt — Admin / Ambulance Company Dashboard

You are a senior full-stack software architect and backend engineer.

Your task is to design and generate the Admin / Company Dashboard for an Ambulance Emergency Booking System.

This agent should focus ONLY on the ambulance company management system.

---

# System Purpose

This dashboard allows ambulance companies to manage their ambulances, receive emergency bookings, track patients, and approve payments.

The system should be secure and accessible only to authenticated administrators.

---

# Authentication

The authentication system must include two distinct flows:

### Sign Up (New Account Creation)
New admins must register with:
- Full Name
- Company Name
- Email Address
- Password
- Confirm Password
- Role Assignment (Super Admin / Admin)

### Login (Returning Users)
Returning admins log in with:
- Email Address
- Password
- **Remember Me** checkbox — stores a persistent session token (e.g. via httpOnly cookie or localStorage JWT with extended expiry) so the user remains logged in across browser sessions

Additional login features:
- Forgot Password / Reset Password link
- Session timeout with auto-logout after inactivity
- "Stay signed in for 30 days" option when Remember Me is checked

Use secure authentication such as:
- JWT authentication (short-lived access tokens + long-lived refresh tokens)
- Role-based access control (RBAC)
- Refresh token rotation for persistent sessions
- Secure httpOnly cookies for Remember Me token storage

---

# Core Admin Features

### 1 Ambulance Registration

Admins must be able to register ambulances with:

- Ambulance Number
- Driver Name
- Driver Contact
- GPS tracking capability
- Ambulance Status

---

### 2 Ambulance Management

Admins must be able to:

- Activate ambulances
- Deactivate ambulances
- Monitor ambulance availability

Ambulance status should automatically change to busy when a booking is accepted.

---

### 3 Booking Management

Admins should see incoming emergency requests including:

- Patient name
- Phone number
- Emergency description
- Patient location on Leaflet + OpenStreetMap 

Admins can then:

- Assign ambulance
- Accept booking
- Dispatch ambulance

---

### 4 Real-Time Tracking

Admins must be able to track:

- Ambulance location
- Patient location

Tracking must be shown live on Leaflet + OpenStreetMap.

Use:

- WebSockets
- Firebase
- Socket.io

---

### 5 Payment Management

Admins should:

- View booking payments
- Confirm or approve payments
- View transaction records

---

### 6 Feedback and Ratings

Admins should be able to view:

- Patient ratings
- Patient feedback
- Service reviews

---

# UI Requirements

Design a professional admin dashboard with pages such as:

1. Admin Sign Up Page
2. Admin Login Page (with Remember Me option)
3. Dashboard Overview / Home Page ← uses ambulance.jpg as background
4. Ambulance Management Page
5. Booking Requests Page
6. Real-Time Tracking Map
7. Payment Management Page
8. Ratings & Feedback Page
9. Reports Generation

Admins should be able to generate reports for operational and financial insights.

Report types:
- Booking Summary Report
- Revenue / Payments Report
- Ambulance Utilization Report
- Driver Performance Report
- Patient & Feedback Report
- Emergency Response Time Report

Filters available on all reports:
- Date range picker (start date / end date)
- Ambulance filter
- Driver filter
- Booking status filter
- Payment status filter

Export formats:
- PDF export (via jsPDF or server-side rendering)
- Excel / CSV export
- Print view

Charts and visualizations (use Chart.js or Recharts):
- Bookings over time (line chart)
- Revenue by period (bar chart)
- Ambulance status breakdown (pie chart)
- Average response time trend
- Rating distribution

The Reports & Analytics page (Page 9) must include:
- Date range selector
- Report type dropdown
- Generate button
- Preview panel
- Export toolbar (PDF / CSV / Print)

Scheduled / automated report delivery is optional but recommended for Super Admin role.

We also have UI images/screenshots.  
Analyze the images and place them in the correct dashboard sections.

